Israel Auctions 1.05 Billion Shekels in Government Securities

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-05-23T12:17:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/israel-auctions-1-05-billion-shekels-in-government-securities.html
Israelâ€™s Ministry of Finance raised a
total of 1.05 billion shekels ($299 million) at debt auctions
today.  It sold 200 million shekels of bonds due in August 2016
paying a coupon of 4.25 percent, according to ministry data on
Bloomberg. It received bids for 1.32 billion shekels. The
government also sold 300 million shekels of bonds maturing in
January 2022 and 250 million shekels of inflation-linked bonds
due in August 2041.  In addition, the Jerusalem-based ministry auctioned 300
million shekels of 148-day notes. It plans to sell 1 billion
shekels in government securities on May 31, bringing the total
sales this month to 3.9 billion shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
